  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nWe have a `POST lighthouse/validators/keystore` endpoint on the VC API:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/65dcdc361b0c91dabe53c886e32aa7952251be68/validator_client/src/http_api/mod.rs#L343\r\n\r\nIt has two issues:\r\n\r\n1. It is not documented in the book.\r\n1. It does not call the [`KeyCache::add`](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/65dcdc361b0c91dabe53c886e32aa7952251be68/validator_client/src/key_cache.rs#L222) function, which means the VC will need to re-decrypt the keypair on the next reboot. This is not ideal.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\n1. Add simple docs showing request/response JSON.\r\n1. Pass the `KeyCache` into the `http_api` and call `KeyCache::add` when new validators are created.",
